Type="String">NAME5</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Hindering</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Wstrzymywanie</Data></Cell></Row><Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0"><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">MOD_6_TEMPLATE</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">NAME6</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Impeding</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Hamowanie</Data></Cell></Row><Row><Cell><Data ss:Type="String"/></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String"/></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String"/></Cell><Cell ss:Index="7"><Data ss:Type="String">In the text below, any inserted strings - anything of the form {text} - is replaced by an integer value for the thing described in the brackets. If the {text} is not followed by a unit - e.g. shields, hitpoints - the icon for the unit is inserted together with the integer. The same holds for symbols - e.g. '+', '%' - which are occasionally inserted together with the integer.</Data></Cell></Row><Row><Cell><Data ss:Type="String"/></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String"/></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String"/></Cell><Cell ss:Index="7"><Data ss:Type="String">For references to game terminology and in-world references, please check the glossary delivered as part of the documentation.</Data></Cell></Row></Table><WorksheetOptions xmlns="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:excel"><Unsynced/><Selected/><TopRowVisible>24</TopRowVisible><Panes><Pane><Number>3</Number><ActiveRow>15</ActiveRow><ActiveCol>2</ActiveCol></Pane></Panes><ProtectObjects>False</ProtectObjects><ProtectScenarios>False</ProtectScenarios></WorksheetOptions></Worksheet></Workbook>